# CHANAKYA Radar

## First-screen principle (mandatory)

Every pixel on the first visible screen must help answer:

> **What should I work on right now?**

If an element does not directly contribute, **relocate below the fold**, **move to the global header**, or **remove** it.

First screen keeps: compact CHANAKYA ticker · hero Radar (blips / ticks / labels) · scope · Opportunity Preview drawer on demand.

Below the fold: KPIs, Direction / Trend / Concern, intelligence cards, legend explanation.

## Architecture

- **Radar | Kanban** switcher lives in the **global header** (beside Notifications, before CHANAKYA AI).
- Tabs preserve scope / KPI focus / selection via shared workspace-tab store.
- Opportunity Preview = right **slide-over** (click outside closes); never permanently shrinks Radar.
- Blip colour = operational status; **distance from centre = stage ageing**; **✓ tick = worked today**.
- Live feed is operational guidance only — does **not** open CHANAKYA AI.
- Page must always **naturally scroll**. No fixed-height lock / clipped content.
- Metric SSOT / Vector / Health scoring — never reimplemented in UI.
- Real-time: `subscribeLoanFilesUpdated` + 60s / `storage` fallback.
- Matrix retired. Kanban cards never draggable.
- Four quadrants: On Track (N) · Follow-up Required (E) · At Risk (S) · Needs Attention (W).
